            . I saw the prisoner on the 31st of May in <placeName id="t18240715-71-crimeloc377">Piccadilly</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18240715-71-crimeloc377" type="placeName" value="Piccadilly"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18240715-71-crimeloc377" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240715-71-off374 t18240715-71-crimeloc377"></join>, near Mr. Ellison's shop - he and the two others took something from the door, which he put under his coat. I crossed over, and collared him in Bond-street, and found this piece of cotton on the ground, behind him - I took it back to Mr. Ellison's, and asked him if he had lost it; he said he believed it was his.</p>
               <p>
            
